# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Since we have to map one character to another, but one or more character can point to same character. So there comes union find to make parent of each character.
After making parent of each character now the answer string is parent of each character in the baseStr.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Iterate over s1 and s2 and make union of character of s1 and s2.
since we want lexicographically small string as answer so instead of giving rank numbers, character have rank acording to dictionary order i.e. a = 0 , b= 1, ... z = 25.
So the union or join function make parent to the character which has less rank.

Now iterate over BaseStr and change each character to its parent character.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$o(n)$$ 
- Space complexity:
