6. Index - 5
s1[5] = 'r'
s2[5] = 's'

'r' == 's' ('r' is lexicographically smaller than 's')

Therefore, 'r' will be a parent of 's'

   k                                            k
    \                                          / \
     r          --- path-compression --->     r   s
      \
       s


7. Parents of characters from 

p -> m
