    boolean[][] isVisited = new boolean[m][n];
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
      for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
        if (!isVisited[i][j]) {
          if (hasCycle(grid, 0, i, j, grid[i][j], isVisited)) return true; // 0 is dummy direction of move.
        }
      }
    }
    return false;
  }

  // @param dir: direction of move. dummy:0, down:1,left:2,up:3,right:4 for each.
  private boolean hasCycle(char[][] grid, int dir, int i, int j, char c, boolean[][] isVisited) {
    if (i < 0 || grid.length <= i || j < 0 || grid[0].length <= j || grid[i][j] != c) return false;
    if (isVisited[i][j]) return true;
    isVisited[i][j] = true;
    return (dir != 3 && hasCycle(grid, 1, i + 1, j, c, isVisited)) // move `down` if previous move was not `up`.
        || (dir != 1 && hasCycle(grid, 3, i - 1, j, c, isVisited)) // move `up` if previous move was not `down`.
        || (dir != 2 && hasCycle(grid, 4, i, j + 1, c, isVisited)) // move `right` if previous move was not `left`.
        || (dir != 4 && hasCycle(grid, 2, i, j - 1, c, isVisited)); // move `left` if previous move was not `right`.
  }
}
```

solutions.content:
Union-find is a popular algorithm to find cycle in graph. The idea is to connect letters of the same value. If we connect and find they already have the same parent, we have found a cycle. Important thing to note here is that rather than connecting in 4 directions, we will connect only to the right and the bottom otherwise the union-find algorithm will wrongly declare a cycle.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean containsCycle(char[][] grid) {
        int n = grid.length, m = grid[0].length;
        UnionFind uf = new UnionFind(n*m);

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                if (i+1 < n && grid[i+1][j] == grid[i][j]) { // connect to bottom
                    if (!uf.union(i*m +j, (i+1)*m + j)) return true;
                }
                if (j+1 < m && grid[i][j+1] == grid[i][j]) { // connect to right
                    if (!uf.union(i*m +j, i*m + (j+1))) return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    class UnionFind {
        int[] parent;
        UnionFind(int sz) {
            parent = new int[sz];
            for (int i = 0; i < sz; i++) parent[i] = i;
        }

        boolean union(int a, int b) {
            int par_a = find(a);
            int par_b = find(b);

            if (par_a == par_b) return false;
            parent[par_a] = par_b;
            return true;
        }

        int find(int a) {
            if (a == parent[a]) return a;
            return parent[a] = find(parent[a]);
        }
    }
}
```

