We can use 3-color to detect whether there is a cycle in graph.
0 -> Never visited
1 -> Visiting
2 -> Visited

Let's say we are traversing in certain path, all node in this path before are colored 1, then 
if we met a node colored 2, means there is a cycle in this path.
If we met a node colored 1, this is the parent node we just visitied.

```class Solution {
    public boolean containsCycle(char[][] grid) {
        int[][] M = new int[grid.length][grid[0].length];
        for(int i = 0; i < grid.length; i ++){
            for(int j = 0; j < grid[0].length; j ++){
                if(M[i][j] == 0 && dfs(grid, grid[i][j], i, j, M)){
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    int[][] dirs = new int[][]{{-1, 0}, {1, 0}, {0, 1}, {0, -1}};
    public boolean dfs(char[][] grid, char c, int i, int j, int[][] M){
        if(i < 0 || i >= grid.length || j < 0 || j >= grid[0].length || grid[i][j] != c){
            return false;
        }
        if(M[i][j] == 2){
            return true;
        }
        if(M[i][j] == 1){
            return false;
        }
        M[i][j] = 1;
        for(int[] dir : dirs){
            int ni = i + dir[0];
            int nj = j + dir[1];
            if(dfs(grid, c, ni, nj, M)){
                return true;
            }
        }
        M[i][j] = 2;
        return false;
    }
}
