solutions.content:
## Idea
General way for Union Find to detect cycle:
+ Get all edges `int[][] edges`.
+ Union each node `u` and `v` in `int[] edge`. Before union `u` and `v`, if they are already in the same component, we find a cycle.

Customized for this problem:
+ No need to get all edges. The graph of this grid is **bi-directional**.  So we can only go **downward and rightward** to traverse all edges. This also avoids adding duplicate edges which might cause false cycle.
## Code
```
class Solution {
    class UF {
        int[] root;
        int[] size;

        public UF(int n) {
            this.root = new int[n];
            this.size = new int[n];

            Arrays.fill(this.size, 1);
            for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
                this.root[i] = i;
            }
        }

        public int find(int x){
            while(x != root[x]){
                root[x] = root[root[x]];
                x = root[x];
            }
            return x;
        }

        public void union(int x, int y){
            int rx = find(x);
            int ry = find(y);

            if(rx == ry) return;

            if(size[rx] > size[ry]){
                root[ry] = rx;
                size[rx] += size[ry];
            }else{
                root[rx] = ry;
                size[ry] += size[rx];
            }
        }

        public boolean isConnected(int x, int y){
            return find(x) == find(y);
        }
    }

    public boolean containsCycle(char[][] grid) {
        // union find : detecting cycle, go over all edges
        // if for new edge, already find (u,v) in same party, cycle detected

        // 1. get edges(cannot have duplicate edges)
        // no need to get

        // 2. union and check
        int n = grid.length;
        int m = grid[0].length;

        UF uf = new UF(n * m);

        // go over downward and rightward to get all edges
        for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == grid[i + 1][j]){
                    if(uf.isConnected(i * m + j, (i + 1) * m + j)) return true;

                    uf.union(i * m + j, (i + 1) * m + j);
                }
            }
        }

        // rightward
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < m - 1; j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == grid[i][j + 1]){
                    if(uf.isConnected(i * m + j, i * m + j + 1)) return true;
                    uf.union(i * m + j, i * m + j + 1);
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

